Conner Family History | CONTRIBUTING
------------------------------------------

Because I want to keep it simple and coherent with previous versions by
the original maintainers, I decided to make this very simple guide of
how to contribute to this project. You are not obliged to follow this,
but you'll ease my job if you do. :)


Open an issue on GitHub
=======================

Open a new issue: https://github.com/snappyapple632/ConneryFamilyHistory/issues/new

If you don't want to open a GitHub account you can contact me on...
Reddit: u/ModulusTheDutchie
Discord: snappyapple632

Open a PR
=========

If you're so inclined, you can also make a branch of this
repo, edit the CSV yourself, and submit a PR to the main
repo. I wouldn't do that honestly, since it's easier
for me to edit the CSV and push commits myself.

Formatting
==========

Since all the outfit data is stored in CSV format, data can be added with a
basic text editor. Commented lines in the CSV file provide basic formatting
instructions.

If you are editing the CSV using LibreOffice Calc, make sure to load the file
with "Quoted field as text" enabled to prevent autoformatting. You may need to
occasionally Ctrl+A the spreadsheet, Format Cells > Set all cell formats to "Text"
to ensure formatting remains consistent and avoid any potential formatting issues.

# Column A: Data type
N - Node; represents the date an outfit was formed.
C - Connector; used to show relationships between outfits.
See "Inter-outfit Relationships".
D - Domain; this type is unused.
SVG - SVG image to be added to the chart. Nodes can be
directly assigned SVG images. DO NOT USE THIS DATA TYPE
FOR OUTFIT LOGOS. Doesn't work, reserved for future use.

You can comment out an entire row by adding a # before
the letter indicating data type.

NODES
# Column B: Outfit Tag and Name

# Column C: Color
Outfit colors are to be assigned to their main (default) faction.
#0138a4 = New Conglomorate
#c90000 = Terran Republic
#662bbf = Vanu Soverignty
#c5c5c5 = Nanite Systems Operative
#000000 = Unknown

# Column D: Parent

Copy and past the name of an outfit's parent outfit into
this column, if applicable. Leave blank if they do not
have a parent.

# Columns E: Start Dates

The ideal start date is when the outfit is formed on PlanetSide 2 itself.
Generally, we want this date to be precise to the month. If you know the
exact day an outfit was created, that's even better!

All dates on the spreadsheet are formatted as YYYY.MM.DD . Dates consisting
of the year only (YYYY), or year and month (YYYY.MM), are also acceptable.

START DATES MUST HAVE AT LEAST A YEAR OF ESTABLISHMENT. If they do not have a
known start date, they cannot be added to the chart.

# Column F: Stop Dates (Deadfits)

If the outfit is known to be presently active, leave this column blank.
This column is also left blank for inactive outfits with no known stop
date, this is meant to be temporary.

People get bored of PlanetSide, or sometimes infighting can occur within
an outfit that results in fallout. Determining stop dates for outfits
tends to be difficult as the means of measuring activity is nebulous.
Additionally, any outfit that is deleted from PlanetSide leaves no trace
(aside from outfit decals, if they had the luxury of owning one).

1. If the outfit has an announcement or statement on discontinuing the
   outfit, use the announcement date as the stop date.
2. If any group of players belonging to an outfit are online on
   PlanetSide in regular intervals, consider that outfit active.
3. If the outfit is still active but no longer plays PlanetSide,
   set the stop date to their last known date of activity + 6 months.
4. If an outfit ceases activity and goes radio silent, set their stop date
   to their last known date of activity.

THERE IS AN EXCEPTION FOR OUTFIT REBRANDS; SEE COLUMN I.

# Column G: Icon

Reserved for future use. Setting this column to "images/outfit_logo.svg"
will add a an outfit's logo next to the node, but I haven't gotten that
to work. Gnuclad has very specific requirements for SVGs so I'm not
bothering with outfit logos for the time being. Gnuclad only accepts SVGs.

# Column H: Description

Any other comments for a particular outfit are left here.

# Column I: Name Change

Outfits that undergo a rebrand (i.e. change their name but otherwise
consist of the same members and outfit ethos), there are columns to
accomodate for name changes. Fill this column with the outfit's
new tag and name.

# Column J: Date of Name Change

The date of the name change will be marked as a smaller dot on the
same branch as the outfit's former name.

# Column K: Name Change Description

Another column for comments.

# Columns L-N:

Repeat of columns I-K to accomodate for multiple name changes.
This can be extended further with nesting brackets.

CONNECTORS

# Column B: From When
The date of which a connector starts.

# Column C: From
Which outfit the connector stems from.

# Column D: To When
Optional date for where the connector ends.
Leaving this blank will set this to the date
in column B.

# Column E: To
Which outfit the connector connects to.

# Column F: Thickness
Set this column as follows:

2 for collaborations (e.g. NE0N, BRAC, 53C, etc.
forming NDC/RALI).

3 for outfit merges (e.g. GOLD, HT, 4x4, BADD, etc.
merging into RBRN/Recursion). Any outfit that has
merged with another should be kept as close together
as reasonably possible. This helps keep connectors short and
clean, which avoids bogging up the chart with vertical lines.
Remember to keep the chart coherent!

# Column G: Color
Set this to the faction color of the outfit in column E.
